ohi-shiny2

simple OHI Shiny app, round 2

Since attending #shinydevcon, couldn’t help applying newfound knowledge towards updating OHI Shiny app, particularly for ohi-global and in anticipation of porting Herman’s htmlwidget of ohi-aster.

See the live demo: .

You can also try this out by running the following in R or RStudio:

# install.packages('shiny')
shiny::runUrl('bbest/ohi-shiny2', subdir='app')

This implementation uses:

  • shinydashboard
  • leaflet

The high resolution global EEZ shapefile was greatly simplified with the excellent rmapshaper::ms_simplify. See prep_rgns.Rmd for specifics.

Improvements are noted throughout the ui.R, server.R and global.R code files with many TODO: statements.
